      "source": "/content/drive/MyDrive/minekg/raw/материалы/PreciousMetalsQuarterly2012SepExecSum.pdf",
      "page": 2,
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "2 Precious Metals Quarterly 2012 Q3 Executive Summary CRU International Limited confidential Other precious metal markets Gold The gold market is expected to remain in fundamental surplus over the next five years. After peaking in 2013, the surplus may then decline during the 2014-17 period. • The world’s gold supplies were largely unchanged in the first half of 2012 as a marginal rise in primary gold supply was largely offset by the fall in supply generated by gold recycling programmes. • Central banks continue to diversify their foreign exchange reserves into gold but their interest has started to wane. • Fabrication demand, jewellery in particular, remains weak but is set to improve in later years on the back of lower prices and rising incomes in many key developing countries. Platinum The platinum market surplus is shrinking fast as troubles with supply deepen. The return to a nearly balanced market is now expected in 2014 but it is unlikely that the fundamental balance will shift into deficit at any point in our forecast period.",
      "doc_type": "материалы",
      "path_year": 2012,
      "path_geo": null,
      "meta_year": 2012
    },
