      "source": "/content/drive/MyDrive/minekg/raw/материалы/PreciousMetalsQuarterly2012SepExecSum.pdf",
      "page": 2,
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "balanced market is now expected in 2014 but it is unlikely that the fundamental balance will shift into deficit at any point in our forecast period. • The decline in platinum mine production is expected to continue in 2013 based in part on the decisions made in 2012 to curtail or defer expansion plans. • Demand from global car manufacturers is expected to strengthen next year thanks to the introduction of Euro VI emissions rules for new vehicles coming into effect on January 1st 2013. • During 2014-17, both supply and demand are likely to grow at approximately the same rate, driven by the new mining projects coming on stream and improved demand on the back of recovering global economy. This should prevent the market from switching into deficit. Palladium Following a significant surplus posted in 2011, the palladium market is set to move into fundamental deficit this year. The deficit is expected to continue widening until the end of our outlook period. • Supply issues in South Africa are having a significant impact on the palladium market. To reflect these developments our outlook for mine output has undergone a major cut.",
      "doc_type": "материалы",
      "path_year": 2012,
      "path_geo": null,
      "meta_year": 2012
    },
