      "text": "also contains a number of excel files containing a wealth of statistical data on gold, silver, platinum and palladium. Should you have any problems with using the CRUOnline website, please contact the helpdesk on Tel +44 20 7903 2113 (09.00–18.00 UK time), or e-mail:- support.cruonline@crugroup.com The following lists the different statistics and downloads that are available to you as a Precious Metals Quarterly subscriber: Quarterly Report  Pdf version of this report  Separate excel workbooks with our forecast tables for gold, silver, platinum and palladium (supply-demand balances, consumption by country and use, mine production by country and operation, scrap generation, more) Market Statistics (all in excel)  COTF futures and options contracts  Gold, silver, platinum and palladium ETF holdings  Prices (precious metals prices and other key indicators)  Statistics (summarised data on prices, exchanges, exchange rates, local prices etc)  Gold, silver, platinum and palladium bullion imports by country  Central Bank gold reserves  UK jewellery hallmarkings  Bombay gold prices and premia  LBMA monthly clearing turnover statistics for gold and silver  Lease rates for gold",
